description: The Jason-1 binary Sensory Geophysical Data Record (SGDR) contains all the same parameters as the binary GDR but also contains the waveforms measured at 20 Hz. The waveforms are needed for retracking purposes that can be use to calculate inland or coastal water levels. This is an expert level product. If you do not require the waveforms then the GDR product is more appropriate, which can be found at http://podaac.jpl.nasa.gov/dataset/JASON-1_L2_OST_GDR_Ver-C_Binary.
name: JASON-1_L2_OST_Sensory_Geophysical_Data_Record_VER-C_BINARY
